1
0:00:31,420 --> 0:00:35,700
外海 世界上最广袤无垠的荒芜之地
The world's greatest wilderness, the open ocean.

2
0:00:37,580 --> 0:00:40,980
海洋占了地球表面的二分之一以上
It covers over half the surface of our planet.

3
0:00:46,620 --> 0:00:50,980
这里没有藏身之处 食物也寥寥无几
Here, there is nowhere to hide and little to eat.

4
0:00:55,340 --> 0:00:58,580
这海洋如同一片沙漠
It's the marine equivalent of a desert.

5
0:01:10,540 --> 0:01:14,340
飞旋海豚在这片海洋里巡查
And patrolling this desert, spinner dolphins.

6
0:01:26,140 --> 0:01:27,740
它们成群结队
They stick together

7
0:01:35,540 --> 0:01:39,620
数量多达5000
in a super-pod, 5,000 strong.

8
0:01:44,540 --> 0:01:48,340
成群出动大大提高了它们的捕食几率
That maximises their chances of finding something to eat.

9
0:01:56,100 --> 0:01:58,260
和生活在海里的其他生物一样
Like all who live here, they

10
0:01:58,260 --> 0:02:00,740
它们必须使出浑身解数
must go to extraordinary length

11
0:02:00,740 --> 0:02:03,900
才能立足于这片汪洋大海
To make their home in the big blue.

12
0:02:26,260 --> 0:02:31,450
这片空旷的海域里很少能检测到生命的迹象
There are rare moments when these empty seas can explore with life.

13
0:02:38,860 --> 0:02:43,260
哥斯达黎加太平洋海岸的灯鱼
Lanternfish, off the pacific coast of costa rica.

14
0:02:43,260 --> 0:02:45,780
和(垂钓时所用的)假饵差不多大
They're scarcely bigger than minnows,

15
0:02:45,780 --> 0:02:50,180
虽然他们体积小 但是他们数量庞大
But what they lack in size they make up for in numbers.

16
0:02:53,380 --> 0:02:56,980
无论在哪儿 它们都是数量庞大的鱼群
They are one of the most numerous fish anywhere.

17
0:03:03,140 --> 0:03:07,640
通常它们只有在晚上才会到海面寻找浮游生物充饥
Normally, they only come to the surface at night to feed on plankton,

18
0:03:07,700 --> 0:03:11,140
但现在它们却在白天游上了海面
But this immense shoal has risen during the day,

19
0:03:11,140 --> 0:03:14,140
几乎可以肯定 它们是为了产卵
Almost certainly in order to spawn.

20
0:03:21,980 --> 0:03:25,340
对于海豚来说 这是一个千载难逢的机会
For the dolphins, this would be a bonanza.

21
0:03:36,700 --> 0:03:41,540
它们利用回声来确定鱼群的位置
They have located the shoal using their echo-sounding calls.

22
0:03:51,820 --> 0:03:54,140
但它们得加快行动
But they have to get to it quickly.

23
0:03:59,220 --> 0:04:01,900
因为别的捕食者也在蠢蠢欲动
They are not the only hunters here.

24
0:04:01,900 --> 0:04:05,100
黄鳍金枪鱼发现了这个灯鱼鱼群
Yellowfin tuna have also detected the shoal.

25
0:04:14,140 --> 0:04:15,340
而它们身后
And behind them,

26
0:04:15,360 --> 0:04:19,100
是翼展两米的魔鬼鱼
with their two-metre wingspans, mobula rays

27
0:04:28,300 --> 0:04:32,260
现在 海洋里的速度担当 旗鱼
Now sailfish, one of the fastest fish in the sea,

28
0:04:32,260 --> 0:04:34,620
也加入了这场捕食的行列
Have joined the chase.

29
0:04:40,940 --> 0:04:44,220
灯鱼随时都会回到深海
The lanternfish may return to the deep at any moment.

30
0:04:51,020 --> 0:04:54,020
但现在海豚已经到达战场
But now the dolphins have got here.

31
0:05:21,660 --> 0:05:25,180
他们游到鱼群的下方 将鱼群逼回海面
They swim beneath the shoal, pinning it to the surface

32
0:05:25,180 --> 0:05:30,020
并迫使鱼群逐渐缩小
And forcing the lanternfish to pack more closely together.

33
0:05:35,700 --> 0:05:39,300
大海开始沸腾了
And now the sea begins to boil.

34
0:05:47,820 --> 0:05:52,300
金枪鱼以每小时40多英里的速度冲入灯鱼群
The tuna charge into the shoal at over 40mph.

35
0:06:22,020 --> 0:06:25,820
游得最慢的魔鬼鱼也到达了战场
The slower-swimming rays arrive at last.

36
0:06:32,100 --> 0:06:34,220
它们张大嘴巴
With their immense mouths agape,

37
0:06:34,220 --> 0:06:37,420
将数百条灯笼鱼吞入腹中
They scoop up the lanternfish by the hundred.

38
0:06:40,900 --> 0:06:44,460
大部分鱼群已被冲散
The shoal has now been largely dispersed,

39
0:06:44,460 --> 0:06:47,380
旗鱼在短短十五分钟内
And the sailfish pick off the survivors.

40
0:06:49,940 --> 0:06:53,180
解决了余下的幸存者
In just 15 minutes,

41
0:06:53,180 --> 0:06:57,580
如今仅剩下银色鱼鳞随波逐流
All that's left is a silvery confetti of scales.

42
0:07:08,100 --> 0:07:12,860
但在这里 如此盛宴难得一遇
But here, such feasts are only too infrequent.

43
0:07:21,380 --> 0:07:25,420
海豚表现出了极大的忍耐力
Whilst the dolphins perform great feats of endurance,

44
0:07:25,420 --> 0:07:28,260
而其余的生物走向了极端
Others are driven to even greater extremes

45
0:07:28,260 --> 0:07:31,540
只为了在这荒漠般的海洋里觅食
To find food in this ocean desert.

46
0:07:49,420 --> 0:07:51,740
一个沉睡的巨人
A sleeping giant.

47
0:07:56,060 --> 0:07:58,060
抹香鲸
A sperm whale.

48
0:08:04,820 --> 0:08:08,820
这个家族正在为下一次捕食养精蓄锐
This family is resting between bouts of feeding.

49
0:08:15,740 --> 0:08:21,480
没人知道这个拥有世界上最大脑袋的生物在做什么梦
Who knows what the owners of the biggest brain in the planet dream about.

50
0:08:28,260 --> 0:08:30,420
这头抹香鲸有个幼崽
One has a calf.

51
0:08:31,500 --> 0:08:33,360
它已经两周岁大了
It's about two weeks old

52
0:08:33,390 --> 0:08:36,140
但还需要母乳喂养
but still dependent on its mother's milk.

53
0:08:36,860 --> 0:08:38,060
它饥肠辘辘
It's hungry.

54
0:08:41,620 --> 0:08:45,780
它利用嘀嗒声来和它的妈妈交流
It communicates with its mother using a pattern of clicks.

55
0:08:52,220 --> 0:08:54,300
但它的妈妈依旧在沉睡
But its mother slumbers on.

56
0:09:00,180 --> 0:09:02,620
小抹香鲸的身上都是吸盘鱼
The calf, covered in sucker fish,

57
0:09:02,620 --> 0:09:05,060
它没法把身上的鱼除掉
of which it can't yet rid itself

58
0:09:05,060 --> 0:09:07,140
所以小抹香鲸要耐心等待
Has to be patient.

59
0:09:33,140 --> 0:09:38,140
鲸鱼抹香鲸睡醒以后神清气爽 继续前行
Sleep over and refreshed, the whales move on.

60
0:09:40,700 --> 0:09:44,200
抹香鲸等不及它们的猎物浮出水面
Sperm whales don't wait for their prey to rise themselves.

61
0:09:45,130 --> 0:09:48,460
于是他们决定潜入深海去寻找
They swim down into the depths to find it.

62
0:09:53,940 --> 0:09:57,620
它们做了一连串的深呼吸
They take a series of heavy breaths

63
0:09:59,740 --> 0:10:02,060
给血液充满氧气
..to saturate their blood with oxygen.

64
0:10:03,980 --> 0:10:07,100
接着向深海游去
Then down they go.

65
0:10:15,100 --> 0:10:19,300
这个抹香鲸家族一起潜入水中寻找乌贼
This entire family dives together in search of squid.

66
0:10:26,940 --> 0:10:30,660
抹香鲸妈妈用尽全身力气向下游
A mother will push her body to the limits of her endurance,

67
0:10:30,660 --> 0:10:34,260
显然它的幼崽有点跟不上它
And already it's hard for her calf to keep up with her.

68
0:10:44,980 --> 0:10:48,540
幼崽竭尽全力靠近妈妈
The calf sticks to its mother as closely as it can

69
0:10:50,460 --> 0:10:56,820
时不时碰碰妈妈 似乎是在寻求安慰
touching her frequently, as if for reassurance.

70
0:11:09,700 --> 0:11:12,660
但是下潜300米深以后
But 300 metres down,

71
0:11:12,660 --> 0:11:16,140
小抹香鲸似乎再也憋不住气了
It seems the calf can't hold its breath any longer.

72
0:11:40,300 --> 0:11:44,820
在长大以前 小抹香鲸不能参加捕猎活动
In their early years, calves are forced to sit out the hunt.

73
0:11:49,820 --> 0:11:52,380
而那些成年抹香鲸继续下潜
The adults continue their dive.

74
0:12:05,220 --> 0:12:07,700
抹香鲸妈妈的嘀嗒声
The mother changes her calls

75
0:12:07,700 --> 0:12:11,220
逐渐变得响亮而急促
Into a series of louder and more rapid clicks.

76
0:12:17,580 --> 0:12:21,500
它正在用声呐搜索成群的乌贼
She's now using sonar to hunt down shoals of squid.

77
0:12:29,860 --> 0:12:33,380
在800米深处 一阵嘀嗒声响起
At 800 metres, a burst of clicks.

78
0:12:41,700 --> 0:12:43,620
接着一片沉寂
Then silence.

79
0:12:46,540 --> 0:12:48,300
她抓到了
She's made a catch.

80
0:12:54,540 --> 0:12:59,300
整个过程长达1小时
that could be way for as much as an hour.

81
0:13:12,590 --> 0:13:15,840
终于 妈妈满载一肚子的乌贼
Finally, the mother returns from the deep

82
0:13:15,880 --> 0:13:19,100
从深海游回来了
with a stomach full of squid.

83
0:13:36,500 --> 0:13:42,260
等了许久 这只小抹香鲸终于可以喝上奶了
After a long wait, this hungry calf can take some milk.

84
0:13:47,620 --> 0:13:51,940
抹香鲸是哺乳动物中产奶量最丰富的
It's one of the richest produced by any mammal,

85
0:13:51,940 --> 0:13:55,940
因此小抹香鲸可以一整天大快朵颐
And the calf guzzles a bathful of it a day.

86
0:14:11,700 --> 0:14:14,360
这些幼崽要花六年的时间
It may be six years before a calf

87
0:14:14,360 --> 0:14:17,660
才能学会深海潜水
masters the art of deep diving

88
0:14:17,660 --> 0:14:21,140
并且独立捕食
And is able to find food for itself.

89
0:14:37,300 --> 0:14:39,720
这片汪洋的空旷
The emptiness of the big blue is

90
0:14:39,720 --> 0:14:42,460
造就了捕食者的艰难处境
what makes life so hard for hunters.

91
0:14:48,660 --> 0:14:50,560
但也正是这空旷
But it's this emptiness

92
0:14:50,670 --> 0:14:53,980
给予了猎物一隅安全的栖息地
that makes it comparatively safe for prey.

93
0:15:02,720 --> 0:15:06,400
一只破壳没几天的海龟宝宝
A baby turtle, hatched just days ago，

94
0:15:06,560 --> 0:15:07,780
正在远离海岸附近这片
is leaving the crowded

95
0:15:07,780 --> 0:15:09,720
拥挤而又危险的水域
Dangerous waters of the coast

96
0:15:09,720 --> 0:15:12,160
朝着外海前行
and heading for the open ocean

97
0:15:19,440 --> 0:15:21,600
直到近几年我们才破解了
Only recently have we begun to solve

98
0:15:21,620 --> 0:15:24,060
海龟宝宝在成年前
The mystery of where baby turtles

99
0:15:24,060 --> 0:15:26,580
去了哪里的谜团
disappear to in their early years.

100
0:15:35,530 --> 0:15:39,120
最初 它们靠植物填饱他们的小肚子
To start with, they fill their little stomach with plants

101
0:15:39,160 --> 0:15:42,140
但很快它们就需要更管饱的食物
But soon they need something more substantial.

102
0:16:02,830 --> 0:16:05,760
每片海域离岸数百英里的地方
Hundreds of miles offshore, in every ocean,

103
0:16:06,020 --> 0:16:09,220
都有许多未谙世事的幼崽
There are communities of young castaways.

104
0:16:17,820 --> 0:16:21,460
漂浮着的任何东西都会吸引它们
So anything that floats attracts them.

105
0:16:28,650 --> 0:16:29,630
一根浮木
A log.

106
0:16:30,340 --> 0:16:32,900
这原木大概已经在海上漂了好几年了
It may have been at sea for several years,

107
0:16:32,900 --> 0:16:36,180
并且已经成了这些小群体的中心了
And it has already become the centre of a small community.

108
0:16:38,300 --> 0:16:41,100
小河豚也是为了这个来到这里
Young puffer fish are here for the same reason.

109
0:16:46,920 --> 0:16:50,300
这根浮木就像一个避难所
A floating log is just the kind of refuge

110
0:16:50,330 --> 0:16:52,680
也正是这只小海龟一直在寻找的
This young turtle has been looking for.

111
0:16:53,820 --> 0:16:57,040
这里不仅有海藻可以吃
Here, there's not only seaweed on which to graze,

112
0:16:57,150 --> 0:16:58,680
还有藤壶
 but barnacles

113
0:17:11,560 --> 0:17:14,560
不过学会躲藏才是至关重要的
But it's important to stay under cover.

114
0:17:20,680 --> 0:17:24,400
一条年轻的丝鲨也漂洋过海来到这里
A young ocean-going silky shark is here, too.

115
0:17:43,040 --> 0:17:45,400
它正在学习分辨什么好吃
It's learning what tastes good.

116
0:17:49,240 --> 0:17:51,360
什么不好吃
And what doesn't.

117
0:18:10,280 --> 0:18:15,420
现在我们知道许多小海龟都会在这样的地方待上好多年 
We now know that many young turtles stay in such places for several years,

118
0:18:16,140 --> 0:18:17,560
直到它们长大成年
until adulthood.

119
0:18:30,720 --> 0:18:35,320
即使这意味着它需要独当一面
Even if it means facing the full force of the high seas.

120
0:18:42,800 --> 0:18:46,240
阳光洒在海上
The sun beating down on the deep blue

121
0:18:46,240 --> 0:18:49,440
提高了海面的温度 促进了海水的蒸发
Warms the surface waters so that they evaporate.

122
0:18:56,960 --> 0:19:00,720
当水蒸气上升时 便凝结成了云
As the vapour rises, it condenses into clouds.

123
0:19:02,680 --> 0:19:07,360
很快风起云涌
They rapidly build into gigantic, burgeoning towers,

124
0:19:07,360 --> 0:19:10,100
最终形成风暴
Which eventually generate violent storms,

125
0:19:10,100 --> 0:19:12,760
有的甚至可以覆盖1000英里的区域
some 1,000 miles across

126
0:19:28,670 --> 0:19:32,460
飓风席卷广阔的海面
Hurricane-force winds sweep across the open ocean,

127
0:19:32,990 --> 0:19:36,240
掀起30多米高的巨浪
Building waves that can rise to 30 metres tall.

128
0:19:50,520 --> 0:19:53,920
在这里 船只会沉入大海 销声匿迹
Out here, ships have been known to sink without trace.

129
0:20:07,960 --> 0:20:11,410
每年有1.3亿集装箱
130 million containers are shipped

130
0:20:11,410 --> 0:20:14,360
装运后横跨大洋
across the oceans every year

131
0:20:16,000 --> 0:20:20,480
然而平均每天就有4个集装箱沉入大海
And on average, four of them fall into the sea every day.

132
0:20:34,760 --> 0:20:38,320
1992年 几个装运着
In 1992, a few were lost

133
0:20:38,320 --> 0:20:41,680
洗澡玩具的集装箱沉入了大海
That contained a consignment of bath toys...

134
0:20:46,560 --> 0:20:51,400
集装箱里装着7000只像这样的塑料鸭
..including 7,000 plastic ducks like these.

135
0:21:02,730 --> 0:21:06,730
它们从阿拉斯加出发 开始了长达1000英里的旅程
They started their travels 1,000 miles off alaska.

136
0:21:10,200 --> 0:21:13,130
有的飘过了太平洋
Some drifted right across the pacific

137
0:21:13,130 --> 0:21:15,360
最终到达澳大利亚
ocean and reached australia.

138
0:21:21,720 --> 0:21:23,600
还有的一路北漂
Others were carried north

139
0:21:23,600 --> 0:21:27,200
停留在俄罗斯和阿拉斯加之间的海岸上
And landed on shores between Russia and Alaska.

140
0:21:29,280 --> 0:21:32,600
更有甚者到达了北极圈
They even found their way into the high Arctic.

141
0:21:46,320 --> 0:21:50,000
有一只洗澡鸭在海上漂流了15年
One duck, having been at sea for 15 years

142
0:21:50,000 --> 0:21:52,280
横跨了三个大洋
And crossing three oceans,

143
0:21:52,280 --> 0:21:56,360
最终到达了苏格兰西海岸
Eventually landed on the west coast of Scotland.

144
0:22:03,600 --> 0:22:07,760
它们的行迹生动地向我们展示了
Their travels vividly illustrate how a network of currents

145
0:22:07,760 --> 0:22:10,700
洋流是如何将各个海洋连成一体
connects all our oceans into one

146
0:22:10,700 --> 0:22:13,280
成为一个巨大的循环系统
gigantic circulatory system

147
0:22:27,980 --> 0:22:30,410
汪洋大海里的许多生物
Many of the inhabitants of the big blue

148
0:22:30,460 --> 0:22:32,200
都依赖洋流
rely on these currents

149
0:22:32,280 --> 0:22:35,080
来找到食物充饥
To carry them to feeding grounds.

150
0:22:49,800 --> 0:22:52,080
一头大青鲨
The blue shark.

151
0:22:56,360 --> 0:22:59,840
它靠着宽大的翼形鱼鳍
It travels over 5,000 miles a year,

152
0:22:59,840 --> 0:23:01,260
顺着洋流
Riding on the currents,

153
0:23:01,280 --> 0:23:04,760
每年游经5000多英里
supported by its broad wing-shaped fins

154
0:23:10,040 --> 0:23:13,400
这头大青鲨大概两个月没有进食了
This one may not have eaten for two months.

155
0:23:20,040 --> 0:23:23,530
不过洋流能带来几英里外
But the currents can carry promising traces of fatty oils

156
0:23:23,530 --> 0:23:27,880
丰厚油脂的的味道 并指引着它前行
from many miles away and will lead it to its next meal.

157
0:23:35,240 --> 0:23:39,520
经过几天的跋涉 食物的味道越来越近
After days of travel, the smell of food gets stronger.

158
0:24:01,240 --> 0:24:04,600
一头被船撞死的鲸
A dead whale, recently struck by a ship.

159
0:24:08,460 --> 0:24:11,560
这堪比一顿饕餮盛宴
This could be a real feast,

160
0:24:11,560 --> 0:24:14,240
不过大青鲨需要小心谨慎
But the blue shark must be cautious.

161
0:24:23,560 --> 0:24:25,880
一条大白鲨
Great white sharks

162
0:24:28,480 --> 0:24:31,080
体重是大青鲨的十倍
ten times heavier than a blue

163
0:24:33,400 --> 0:24:36,840
对这头鲸鱼的尸体也蠢蠢欲动
are highly possessive around a whale carcass.

164
0:25:03,440 --> 0:25:07,480
大白鲨迫不及待地吃起了高能量的鲸脂
Great whites are eager to feed on energy-rich whale blubber,

165
0:25:07,480 --> 0:25:10,880
现在我们知道了这是它们的主要食物
Which we now know forms a major part of their diet.

166
0:25:23,240 --> 0:25:25,640
一旦大白鲨吃饱喝足
Once the great white has had its fill,

167
