344
0:48:30,880 --> 0:48:35,920
他们搬得似乎还不够远
To escape the effects of what we are doing to their world.

345
0:49:03,200 --> 0:49:04,930
在浩瀚的海洋里
The biggest challenge of filming

346
0:49:04,930 --> 0:49:06,720
拍摄最大的挑战是
in the vastness in the open ocean.

347
0:49:06,720 --> 0:49:08,600
寻找你的目标
Is to find your subject...

348
0:49:13,120 --> 0:49:15,640
蓝色星球摄制组想要拍摄
..and the blue planet team wanted to film

349
0:49:15,640 --> 0:49:18,520
其中一件最难拍的东西
One of the most elusive of them all,

350
0:49:18,520 --> 0:49:22,560
就是极少被目击到的 沸腾的海洋
The rarely witnessed "boiling sea".

351
0:49:27,400 --> 0:49:29,380
直到现在 这种海豚集群进食的场景
Until now, this feeding frenzy

352
0:49:29,380 --> 0:49:31,360
仍然具有传奇色彩
has been the stuff of legends.

353
0:49:36,800 --> 0:49:38,880
在澳大利亚东北部
After some promising sightings off

354
0:49:38,880 --> 0:49:40,960
有人声称看见过这种场景
the north-east cost of Australia

355
0:49:40,960 --> 0:49:42,720
于是摄制组开始着手调查
The team heads out to investigate.

356
0:49:46,840 --> 0:49:49,600
我们知道这事无比非凡 我们知道就在那儿
We know it's a phenomenon, we know it's out there,

357
0:49:49,600 --> 0:49:51,360
科学家们有文件记录过
The scientists have documented it,

358
0:49:51,360 --> 0:49:53,520
渔民告诉了我们
The fishermen have told us about it,

359
0:49:53,520 --> 0:49:57,520
所以我们知道肯定会出现 但是没人会疯狂到
So we know it's happening, but no-one has been crazy enough

360
0:49:57,520 --> 0:49:59,340
试着去那里
To attempt to go out there and

361
0:49:59,340 --> 0:50:01,360
拍下这些画面 除了我们
actually film it, except for us

362
0:50:03,200 --> 0:50:05,520
摄制组开始在太平洋上
The team start their search 100

363
0:50:05,520 --> 0:50:07,840
100英里的海域进行搜索
miles out in the pacific ocean

364
0:50:10,880 --> 0:50:13,600
之所以叫 沸腾的海洋 是因为金枪鱼
The reason it's called a "boiling sea" is that the tuna

365
0:50:13,600 --> 0:50:16,480
从水下冲上来
Are actually coming out of the water

366
0:50:16,480 --> 0:50:18,360
袭击灯鱼群
And attacking lanternfish and it

367
0:50:18,360 --> 0:50:20,080
溅起了白色的浪花
creates a lot of white water

368
0:50:23,240 --> 0:50:25,400
为了拍摄沸腾的海洋
To film the boiling seas,

369
0:50:25,400 --> 0:50:29,040
摄制组必须先找到一大群饵鱼
The team must first find a large shoal of bait fish,

370
0:50:29,040 --> 0:50:31,400
很可能就是
Most likely to be lanternfish

371
0:50:31,400 --> 0:50:33,720
晚上浮出水面产卵的灯鱼
Rising to the surface at night to spawn.

372
0:50:35,400 --> 0:50:36,640
几天之后
A few days out,

373
0:50:36,640 --> 0:50:38,840
艾德里安认为她可能在
Adrian thinks he may have spotted a

374
0:50:38,860 --> 0:50:42,280
回声探测器上发现一个巨大的鱼群
giant shoal on the echo sounder

375
0:50:42,280 --> 0:50:45,120
我们看到是是一个非常 非常密集的层次
What we're seeing is a very, very dense layer

376
0:50:45,120 --> 0:50:47,160
大约在200米深的地方
At about 200 metres' water depth.

377
0:50:47,160 --> 0:50:50,080
因此 这所表明的事实是
And so, the fact that we've got this would suggest

378
0:50:50,080 --> 0:50:55,160
我们发现了一个非常深且密集的鱼群
That we have a very deep and dense layer of fish.

379
0:50:56,010 --> 0:50:59,470
在辽阔海洋中拍摄的最好的方法之一
One of the best ways to film at such depths in the open ocean

